Unfortunately, I do not recommend visiting this Dunkin'. The service as a whole is inconsistent. One day the line will be out the door, and the next day it may appear reasonable, only to expand to the door again. One day you may get what you ordered, albeit after waiting a while; the next day you may get someone else's order, or the wrong order. One day the cash registers may be working just fine, and the next day one is out of commission.  Some of the employees are as nice as can be, and certainly try their best with what they have. But it appears that they don't have the leadership and training they need to give consistent decent service. I also understand that machines break once in a while, but they shouldn't break often. I understand that running a business is tricky. But the type of bad service I described above can be minimized, at the very least, with decent management.  So, what prompted me too write this review in the first place? Today I visited with plenty of time to spare. I put in my order. I paid. I tried waiting patiently for my order despite the printing machine not working, despite getting someone else's order initially, and despite my friend getting her order first even though she ordered after me. I ordered a bacon, egg, and cheese wake-up wrap and 1 order of hash browns. No drink. My friend ordered a drink and a breakfast sandwich. Because I knew I was already going to be late for work, I left without getting what I paid for.  This Dunkin' has lost my business indefinitely. I have given them more than enough of my money, patience, and understanding.  If you would still like to visit this Dunkin', my word of advice is to get there with more than half an hour to spare and to always get a receipt in case you get the wrong order, or never get your order at all. As for me, I'm simply done with this place.

If there’s one reason why I go to Dunkin, it’s because I expect consistency and speed.  This Dunkin fails in both aspects, ironically with impeccable consistency. When the machines are actually working and the servers actually care (both of which are increasingly unlikely scenarios), it takes ages to get even a small coffee. When you get that small coffee, it is either made incorrectly or tastes awful.  This Dunkin fails spectacularly. Poor service, broken machines, awful serving time. The list goes on.  Find another Dunkin. I assure you this one isn’t good.
